article.headline: Colgate 70, Maine 62
article.story: EDS: Colgate 70, Maine 62 HAMILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Kyle Roemer scored 17 points to lead Colgate to a 70-62 win over Maine Wednesday night at Cotterell Court. Colgate (8-5) wins its second straight, while Maine (4-9) drops its fifth straight game. Other Colgate players in double figures were Tim Pounds with 14 points and Kendall Chones with 11. Maine was led by Mark Socoby with a game-high 22 points and Junior Bernal with 18. Colgate jumped out to a 9-2 lead before increasing its advantage to 13 points, 25-12, with 6:21 remaining in the first half. Pounds had six points in a nine-point run for the Raiders. Colgate led at halftime 33-26, but Maine scored the first five points of the second half to get to within two points. The Raiders went on an 8-2 run to open an eight-point advantage with 14:35 remaining. The closest the Black Bears would come the rest of the way was four points, 41-37, with 13:16 left. They went without a field goal for over 11 minutes in the second half.
